      • next

        public NodeList.Node<T> next()
        Gets the next NodeList.Node in the NodeList. Returns null for the last NodeList.Node, or for a NodeList.Node that has been removed from its NodeList. This is an O(1) operation.
        Returns:
        the next NodeList.Node in the NodeList

      • owner

        public NodeList<T> owner()
        Gets the NodeList that contains the NodeList.Node. Returns null if the NodeList.Node has been removed from its NodeList. Otherwise, returns the same valid object throughout the lifetime of the NodeList.Node.
        Returns:
        the NodeList that contains the NodeList.Node

      • previous

        public NodeList.Node<T> previous()
        Gets the previous NodeList.Node in the NodeList. Returns null for the first NodeList.Node, or for a NodeList.Node that has been removed from its NodeList. This is an O(1) operation.
        Returns:
        the previous NodeList.Node in the NodeList

      • setValue

        public void setValue(T value)
        Sets the element stored in the NodeList.Node. Calling setValue(T) will not cause existing iterators to throw ConcurrentModificationException as it involves no structural change.
        Parameters:
        value - the element stored in the NodeList.Node
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if value is null

      • value

        public T value()
        Gets the element stored in the NodeList.Node. Remains unchanged when a NodeList.Node is removed from its NodeList.
        Returns:
        the element stored in the NodeList.Node
